WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.076 align:middle line:90%
[ Music ]

00:00:22.757 --> 00:00:24.358 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina Meredith: One
of the biggest challenges

00:00:24.358 --> 00:00:27.828 align:middle line:84%
to making cohesive and
functional societies is a lack

00:00:27.828 --> 00:00:31.532 align:middle line:84%
of genuine communication
and egoless participation.

00:00:31.532 --> 00:00:34.135 align:middle line:84%
Healing a Broken World
offers strategies

00:00:34.135 --> 00:00:35.536 align:middle line:90%
that are clearer than most.

00:00:35.536 --> 00:00:39.673 align:middle line:84%
Why? Because the consultants are
beings from off planet cultures

00:00:39.673 --> 00:00:41.876 align:middle line:90%
or interdimensional beings.

00:00:41.876 --> 00:00:45.112 align:middle line:84%
As they observe this fragile
period of history we're in,

00:00:45.112 --> 00:00:47.782 align:middle line:84%
they see from perhaps a
more detached perspective

00:00:47.782 --> 00:00:51.519 align:middle line:84%
that the fixes are doable if
we can use some compassion

00:00:51.519 --> 00:00:54.522 align:middle line:84%
for one another and leave
our agendas out of it.

00:00:54.522 --> 00:00:57.691 align:middle line:84%
Byron Belitsos is the
co-author and publisher

00:00:57.691 --> 00:01:00.895 align:middle line:84%
of Healing a Broken World
which is based on a vast body

00:01:00.895 --> 00:01:04.498 align:middle line:84%
of work called the Urantia
Book, the advice that's given

00:01:04.498 --> 00:01:07.001 align:middle line:84%
in a sound and enlightening
manner I have to say.

00:01:07.001 --> 00:01:08.969 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of
people say what?

00:01:08.969 --> 00:01:11.439 align:middle line:84%
We're having essentially
teams built

00:01:11.439 --> 00:01:13.574 align:middle line:84%
with off planet cultures
involved?

00:01:13.574 --> 00:01:15.109 align:middle line:84%
Sounds kind of far out
to a lot of people.

00:01:15.109 --> 00:01:16.177 align:middle line:90%
Not to me.

00:01:16.177 --> 00:01:17.578 align:middle line:84%
But we're going to
explain how it all came

00:01:17.578 --> 00:01:19.113 align:middle line:84%
about because it has
a lot of traction,

00:01:19.113 --> 00:01:20.915 align:middle line:84%
and there's some
pretty high up people

00:01:20.915 --> 00:01:23.517 align:middle line:84%
who have been using this
work for a very long time.

00:01:23.517 --> 00:01:26.520 align:middle line:84%
So first of all let's start
out with what is Urantia?

00:01:26.520 --> 00:01:28.889 align:middle line:84%
What was the Urantia Book
and then how it came about.

00:01:28.889 --> 00:01:29.722 align:middle line:90%
And you have time.

00:01:29.722 --> 00:01:31.125 align:middle line:90%
Just lay it out there for us.

00:01:31.125 --> 00:01:32.626 align:middle line:84%
>> Byron Belitsos: Alright,
I'm going to lay it out,

00:01:32.626 --> 00:01:34.228 align:middle line:84%
and I'm very delighted
to be on the program.

00:01:34.228 --> 00:01:35.996 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much.

00:01:35.996 --> 00:01:37.264 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: I'm happy
you're here, too.

00:01:37.264 --> 00:01:39.133 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Urantia is
actually purportedly the name

00:01:39.133 --> 00:01:42.502 align:middle line:84%
of our planet according
to the celestials.

00:01:42.502 --> 00:01:44.438 align:middle line:90%
So up there when they looked

00:01:44.438 --> 00:01:46.307 align:middle line:84%
down upon earth they
called it Urantia.

00:01:46.307 --> 00:01:47.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: What's it mean?

00:01:47.740 --> 00:01:51.445 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: It is simply the
name designated for the planet.

00:01:51.445 --> 00:01:54.482 align:middle line:84%
You could derive it from
the Greek word uranos

00:01:54.482 --> 00:01:56.383 align:middle line:90%
which means the heavens.

00:01:56.383 --> 00:01:57.585 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Okay, okay.

00:01:57.585 --> 00:01:59.787 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: But they
never [inaudible] I happen

00:01:59.787 --> 00:02:01.922 align:middle line:90%
to know Greek.

00:02:01.922 --> 00:02:03.257 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Okay.

00:02:03.257 --> 00:02:04.959 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: So that's why
they call it the Urantia Book.

00:02:04.959 --> 00:02:07.294 align:middle line:90%
It's a book for the planet.

00:02:07.294 --> 00:02:09.964 align:middle line:84%
And it has a planetary
perspective

00:02:09.964 --> 00:02:11.532 align:middle line:90%
that was premature you might say

00:02:11.532 --> 00:02:14.201 align:middle line:84%
because we didn't really
have planetary evolution

00:02:14.201 --> 00:02:18.706 align:middle line:84%
or perspectives in the 20s and
30s when this came through.

00:02:18.706 --> 00:02:20.207 align:middle line:90%
But that's when it came through.

00:02:20.207 --> 00:02:24.178 align:middle line:84%
So it's one of the
earliest statements

00:02:24.178 --> 00:02:28.149 align:middle line:84%
of a holistic planetary and
off planetary perspective

00:02:28.149 --> 00:02:30.584 align:middle line:90%
on humanity in our history.

00:02:30.584 --> 00:02:31.418 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Right.

00:02:31.418 --> 00:02:32.987 align:middle line:90%
And this was a channeled work

00:02:32.987 --> 00:02:36.457 align:middle line:84%
in a time long before
certainly the word channeling

00:02:36.457 --> 00:02:39.793 align:middle line:84%
or the concept of channeling
was known to society at large.

00:02:39.793 --> 00:02:45.332 align:middle line:84%
Although there have always been
people who were able to dial in

00:02:45.332 --> 00:02:47.902 align:middle line:84%
and receive information
from the other realms.

00:02:47.902 --> 00:02:51.872 align:middle line:84%
This is amazing because
of the sheer volume

00:02:51.872 --> 00:02:53.207 align:middle line:90%
of work that came through.

00:02:53.207 --> 00:02:54.441 align:middle line:90%
So let's talk about that.

00:02:54.441 --> 00:02:56.443 align:middle line:90%
Who did it come through?

00:02:56.443 --> 00:02:57.478 align:middle line:90%
How did it come through?

00:02:57.478 --> 00:03:00.047 align:middle line:84%
Over what period of
time and so forth?

00:03:00.047 --> 00:03:01.882 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: A lot
of it is a mystery

00:03:01.882 --> 00:03:03.217 align:middle line:90%
as to how it came through.

00:03:03.217 --> 00:03:06.020 align:middle line:84%
It technically shouldn't really
be called a channeled work

00:03:06.020 --> 00:03:11.258 align:middle line:84%
because the lore about this is
that it did not get channeled

00:03:11.258 --> 00:03:14.595 align:middle line:84%
through a person
but it appeared.

00:03:14.595 --> 00:03:15.596 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Okay.

00:03:15.596 --> 00:03:17.264 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Now,
that's not proven.

00:03:17.264 --> 00:03:20.034 align:middle line:84%
There's historians
working on this,

00:03:20.034 --> 00:03:21.735 align:middle line:84%
but there's not much
documentation.

00:03:21.735 --> 00:03:23.938 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: It appeared
how and where?

00:03:23.938 --> 00:03:25.940 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: To a
group in Chicago.

00:03:25.940 --> 00:03:27.374 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: But how
did it appear?

00:03:27.374 --> 00:03:28.642 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Literally
the papers

00:03:28.642 --> 00:03:31.879 align:middle line:84%
or chapters would
appear, materialize.

00:03:31.879 --> 00:03:34.748 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Without
human participation?

00:03:34.748 --> 00:03:36.116 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Without
human intervention known.

00:03:36.116 --> 00:03:38.419 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: But wasn't there one
particular person that a lot

00:03:38.419 --> 00:03:40.955 align:middle line:84%
of it they were in
communion with regularly?

00:03:40.955 --> 00:03:42.156 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: There
was one particular one

00:03:42.156 --> 00:03:43.757 align:middle line:84%
but actually a group of
six, and they're known

00:03:43.757 --> 00:03:45.125 align:middle line:90%
as the contact commission.

00:03:45.125 --> 00:03:48.161 align:middle line:84%
And that work was around
-- the core person,

00:03:48.161 --> 00:03:49.296 align:middle line:90%
the kind of chairman

00:03:49.296 --> 00:03:51.197 align:middle line:84%
of the group was a guy
named Sadler [phonetic],

00:03:51.197 --> 00:03:53.634 align:middle line:84%
a professor at University
of Chicago and a physician

00:03:53.634 --> 00:03:56.170 align:middle line:84%
who was a visionary but
also a real scientist.

00:03:56.170 --> 00:03:58.472 align:middle line:84%
He actually studied
with Freud at one point.

00:03:58.472 --> 00:04:02.109 align:middle line:84%
So he was well known and
a very prolific author.

00:04:02.109 --> 00:04:04.678 align:middle line:84%
So that's why some people think,
well, he wrote this thing.

00:04:04.678 --> 00:04:07.348 align:middle line:84%
But he was actually a skeptic
who was brought in to try

00:04:07.348 --> 00:04:08.882 align:middle line:90%
to debunk what was happening.

00:04:08.882 --> 00:04:11.819 align:middle line:84%
They were having contacts
through a contact person

00:04:11.819 --> 00:04:14.788 align:middle line:84%
who you could imagine being
like Edgar Cayce who was asleep

00:04:14.788 --> 00:04:16.590 align:middle line:84%
and these voices
would come through.

00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:18.592 align:middle line:84%
But that's not how the
Urantia Book came through.

00:04:18.592 --> 00:04:22.830 align:middle line:84%
That was how the celestials
oriented them to here we are,

00:04:22.830 --> 00:04:25.099 align:middle line:84%
we want to get to know you,
we want you to get to know us,

00:04:25.099 --> 00:04:28.035 align:middle line:84%
and then we're going to give you
a revelation a little bit later.

00:04:28.035 --> 00:04:33.007 align:middle line:84%
So on a particular day they
started, it was February 11,

00:04:33.007 --> 00:04:39.880 align:middle line:84%
1924, and from 24 until 1942
this material came through.

00:04:39.880 --> 00:04:42.316 align:middle line:84%
It would come through
one paper at a time.

00:04:42.316 --> 00:04:45.486 align:middle line:84%
There was 196 of them
so it's pretty big.

00:04:45.486 --> 00:04:47.855 align:middle line:84%
They would read it, they
being this core group,

00:04:47.855 --> 00:04:49.790 align:middle line:84%
and then expand it to
a much bigger group.

00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:51.292 align:middle line:84%
And then they would
feed questions back

00:04:51.292 --> 00:04:53.394 align:middle line:90%
through the contact personality.

00:04:53.394 --> 00:04:55.429 align:middle line:90%
We don't know who that is.

00:04:55.429 --> 00:04:57.631 align:middle line:84%
And they'd feed them
back to the celestials

00:04:57.631 --> 00:05:00.934 align:middle line:84%
and they would rewrite the
chapter based on the questions.

00:05:00.934 --> 00:05:02.636 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And then the
papers just would --

00:05:02.636 --> 00:05:04.938 align:middle line:84%
the lore is that the
papers would disappear?

00:05:04.938 --> 00:05:05.873 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: Disappear.

00:05:05.873 --> 00:05:08.909 align:middle line:84%
Because it's kind
of inconceivable

00:05:08.909 --> 00:05:13.547 align:middle line:84%
that anybody could write this or
even channel it through the mind

00:05:13.547 --> 00:05:17.818 align:middle line:84%
because it's so superb in
its language and coherence.

00:05:17.818 --> 00:05:19.019 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: But I
mean the essence

00:05:19.019 --> 00:05:22.089 align:middle line:84%
of a pure channel is there
is none of them in it.

00:05:22.089 --> 00:05:24.058 align:middle line:84%
Their mind isn't
participating in it.

00:05:24.058 --> 00:05:25.926 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: I haven't
seen one yet.

00:05:25.926 --> 00:05:26.560 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: You haven't?

00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:27.494 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: No.

00:05:27.494 --> 00:05:29.096 align:middle line:84%
I've been to many,
many channels.

00:05:29.096 --> 00:05:30.197 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yes.

00:05:30.197 --> 00:05:30.898 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: And there's
a little bit of them

00:05:30.898 --> 00:05:32.366 align:middle line:90%
and also their cultures,

00:05:32.366 --> 00:05:35.669 align:middle line:84%
skews of their linguistic
capabilities also.

00:05:35.669 --> 00:05:37.738 align:middle line:84%
The Urantia Book is
just it's so vast

00:05:37.738 --> 00:05:39.740 align:middle line:84%
that it can't come
from a single mind.

00:05:39.740 --> 00:05:40.808 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: No, not from a mind.

00:05:40.808 --> 00:05:42.943 align:middle line:90%
I understand what you're saying.

00:05:42.943 --> 00:05:44.311 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:05:44.311 --> 00:05:47.348 align:middle line:84%
So what happened to this doctor
after he came to debunk it?

00:05:47.348 --> 00:05:51.585 align:middle line:84%
How long did it take before
he became a full blown member

00:05:51.585 --> 00:05:52.753 align:middle line:90%
of the six?

00:05:52.753 --> 00:05:53.987 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: A number
of years actually.

00:05:53.987 --> 00:05:55.689 align:middle line:84%
I mean he was participating,
and he was kind

00:05:55.689 --> 00:05:58.092 align:middle line:84%
of the guy holding
the space for this.

00:05:58.092 --> 00:06:01.628 align:middle line:84%
But there was a certain point
where he just said I've got

00:06:01.628 --> 00:06:02.329 align:middle line:90%
to throw in the towel.

00:06:02.329 --> 00:06:03.530 align:middle line:90%
This is so brilliant,

00:06:03.530 --> 00:06:04.732 align:middle line:84%
I just can't believe
anybody could make this up,

00:06:04.732 --> 00:06:06.800 align:middle line:90%
and it was in his field.

00:06:06.800 --> 00:06:09.903 align:middle line:84%
And his field was
mainly psychiatry.

00:06:09.903 --> 00:06:14.641 align:middle line:84%
And they depicted the
psychology of the 12 apostles.

00:06:14.641 --> 00:06:17.277 align:middle line:84%
He said it was such a brilliant
depiction of the 12 apostles

00:06:17.277 --> 00:06:19.246 align:middle line:84%
that just no human
could come up with that.

00:06:19.246 --> 00:06:21.181 align:middle line:84%
So that's when he
said I'm all in.

00:06:21.181 --> 00:06:22.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Okay, do you mind
just sharing a teensy bit

00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:23.984 align:middle line:90%
about that.

00:06:23.984 --> 00:06:25.319 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: About
that particular --

00:06:25.319 --> 00:06:26.386 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Yeah, just about
that, that it impressed him

00:06:26.386 --> 00:06:28.622 align:middle line:90%
so much about the apostles.

00:06:28.622 --> 00:06:31.625 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: They depict them
as very flawed individuals.

00:06:31.625 --> 00:06:33.894 align:middle line:84%
And they show all
these different sides.

00:06:33.894 --> 00:06:40.267 align:middle line:84%
I mean Peter had a really big
kind of flawed side of kind

00:06:40.267 --> 00:06:45.272 align:middle line:84%
of egocentrism and fear
that was very deep.

00:06:45.272 --> 00:06:48.108 align:middle line:84%
And he really didn't want to
get out there and do what he did

00:06:48.108 --> 00:06:50.144 align:middle line:84%
which he was the
key spokesperson.

00:06:50.144 --> 00:06:54.982 align:middle line:84%
And this other part of him was
a very talented public speaker.

00:06:54.982 --> 00:06:58.185 align:middle line:84%
So he had a very
conflicted inner life

00:06:58.185 --> 00:07:01.889 align:middle line:84%
until much later it says that he
finally synthesized these parts

00:07:01.889 --> 00:07:04.191 align:middle line:84%
of himself and became
the great Apostle Peter.

00:07:04.191 --> 00:07:05.425 align:middle line:90%
So that's one example.

00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:06.560 align:middle line:90%
John is another one.

00:07:06.560 --> 00:07:07.661 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Yeah, what
did they say about John?

00:07:07.661 --> 00:07:09.463 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people are
fascinated with John.

00:07:09.463 --> 00:07:11.632 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Oh, I just
love the depiction of John.

00:07:11.632 --> 00:07:13.600 align:middle line:90%
John was mild mannered.

00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:17.004 align:middle line:84%
He was pretty shy and
young, and he was kind

00:07:17.004 --> 00:07:20.274 align:middle line:90%
of pulled along by the others.

00:07:20.274 --> 00:07:24.511 align:middle line:84%
But he had a tremendous
kind of philosophic capacity

00:07:24.511 --> 00:07:25.913 align:middle line:90%
that developed and unfolded.

00:07:25.913 --> 00:07:28.582 align:middle line:84%
And that's why the Gospel
of John is different

00:07:28.582 --> 00:07:30.017 align:middle line:90%
because of who John was.

00:07:30.017 --> 00:07:30.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Right.

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:32.152 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: But
it was very hidden

00:07:32.152 --> 00:07:34.454 align:middle line:84%
when he was a young
man with Jesus.

00:07:34.454 --> 00:07:36.490 align:middle line:84%
So they talk about
how this was buried

00:07:36.490 --> 00:07:38.125 align:middle line:90%
and how it came forward later.

00:07:38.125 --> 00:07:39.893 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Okay, that's
just a little tease.

00:07:39.893 --> 00:07:41.829 align:middle line:84%
I know that this
is -- how fat is

00:07:41.829 --> 00:07:43.463 align:middle line:90%
that book, the Book of Urantia?

00:07:43.463 --> 00:07:45.199 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: 2,097 pages.

00:07:45.199 --> 00:07:46.633 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: 2,097 pages.

00:07:46.633 --> 00:07:49.269 align:middle line:84%
So if we want to get into it
then we can study the rest

00:07:49.269 --> 00:07:50.637 align:middle line:90%
on our own.

00:07:50.637 --> 00:07:52.773 align:middle line:84%
I'm not suggesting that you lay
out too much of it right now

00:07:52.773 --> 00:07:55.209 align:middle line:84%
because we want to lead
toward the subject at hand

00:07:55.209 --> 00:07:58.078 align:middle line:84%
because they had some pretty
profound advice about it.

00:07:58.078 --> 00:08:02.616 align:middle line:84%
So I would like to -- as we
start moving toward the how

00:08:02.616 --> 00:08:05.319 align:middle line:84%
to heal a broken
world let's just say

00:08:05.319 --> 00:08:09.489 align:middle line:84%
that the world became broken not
necessarily of its own accord.

00:08:09.489 --> 00:08:12.759 align:middle line:84%
Because they do acknowledge that
there have been other species

00:08:12.759 --> 00:08:16.463 align:middle line:84%
that have been here and have
interfered as well as assisted.

00:08:16.463 --> 00:08:19.466 align:middle line:84%
And maybe you can talk a
little bit about that part.

00:08:19.466 --> 00:08:22.336 align:middle line:84%
Often it's called
the fall of humanity.

00:08:22.336 --> 00:08:23.837 align:middle line:90%
What actually happened?

00:08:23.837 --> 00:08:27.608 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: The Urantia Book
affirms that there was a fall.

00:08:27.608 --> 00:08:30.744 align:middle line:84%
But the fall is presented
in mythic terms

00:08:30.744 --> 00:08:33.146 align:middle line:90%
in the Bible and Genesis.

00:08:33.146 --> 00:08:37.918 align:middle line:84%
But much of Genesis does
point to the true history.

00:08:37.918 --> 00:08:42.189 align:middle line:84%
And what we, Urantia
believers think and believe is

00:08:42.189 --> 00:08:45.225 align:middle line:84%
that this is the true
history of what happened.

00:08:45.225 --> 00:08:46.994 align:middle line:90%
And there are two big phases.

00:08:46.994 --> 00:08:49.463 align:middle line:84%
There was a really,
really distant phase

00:08:49.463 --> 00:08:55.002 align:middle line:84%
when an off planet group,
kind of hybrid, angelic human,

00:08:55.002 --> 00:09:01.041 align:middle line:84%
come to present civilization
and the basic aspects of living

00:09:01.041 --> 00:09:03.010 align:middle line:90%
in civilization to humanity.

00:09:03.010 --> 00:09:06.246 align:middle line:90%
It was 500,000 years ago.

00:09:06.246 --> 00:09:09.449 align:middle line:84%
That particular group
went astray.

00:09:09.449 --> 00:09:10.984 align:middle line:90%
It went to the dark side.

00:09:10.984 --> 00:09:13.153 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: You're talking
500,000 years ago it starts

00:09:13.153 --> 00:09:16.924 align:middle line:84%
lining up with what are
often called the Anunnaki,

00:09:16.924 --> 00:09:18.191 align:middle line:90%
[inaudible] and so forth.

00:09:18.191 --> 00:09:20.661 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: That's why
Urantians tend to be friendly

00:09:20.661 --> 00:09:22.396 align:middle line:90%
to the theory of the Anunnaki.

00:09:22.396 --> 00:09:23.597 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yes.

00:09:23.597 --> 00:09:27.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: The Anunnaki
is mainly seen at ETs.

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:31.305 align:middle line:84%
The Urantia version is much more
sophisticated, and it's located

00:09:31.305 --> 00:09:33.907 align:middle line:84%
in a cosmology that's also
far more sophisticated

00:09:33.907 --> 00:09:36.677 align:middle line:90%
and more scientific I believe.

00:09:36.677 --> 00:09:40.781 align:middle line:84%
But we can use the term Anunnaki
because that refers to a kind

00:09:40.781 --> 00:09:46.954 align:middle line:84%
of rogue group that then kind
of intersplice their genes

00:09:46.954 --> 00:09:48.255 align:middle line:90%
so to speak with humans.

00:09:48.255 --> 00:09:50.724 align:middle line:84%
And the Urantia Book
says that did happen.

00:09:50.724 --> 00:09:53.460 align:middle line:84%
This group that incarnated,
these are avatars actually,

00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:57.698 align:middle line:84%
there were 100 of them,
began to interbreed

00:09:57.698 --> 00:10:00.367 align:middle line:90%
with the natives way back then,

00:10:00.367 --> 00:10:02.736 align:middle line:84%
and that's where
this legend begins.

00:10:02.736 --> 00:10:05.539 align:middle line:84%
But there's yet another
group that comes later

00:10:05.539 --> 00:10:09.309 align:middle line:84%
in another interbreeding
program that also went astray.

00:10:09.309 --> 00:10:11.645 align:middle line:84%
And that's the one
that's not easy to talk

00:10:11.645 --> 00:10:15.549 align:middle line:84%
about because it's Adam and
Eve which is considered mythic.

00:10:15.549 --> 00:10:16.817 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: No, please
go into detail.

00:10:16.817 --> 00:10:19.987 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: That's an
amazing section on Adam

00:10:19.987 --> 00:10:21.955 align:middle line:90%
and Eve that's very eye opening.

00:10:21.955 --> 00:10:25.459 align:middle line:84%
Because you take Adam and Eve it
sounds like it's a fairy story.

00:10:25.459 --> 00:10:29.763 align:middle line:84%
But this explains that every
planet has to have an Adam

00:10:29.763 --> 00:10:32.132 align:middle line:84%
and an Eve who are
beings who come

00:10:32.132 --> 00:10:35.669 align:middle line:84%
to bring a genetic
upliftment to the planet.

00:10:35.669 --> 00:10:37.604 align:middle line:84%
They're actually
going to interbreed.

00:10:37.604 --> 00:10:38.538 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Right.

00:10:38.538 --> 00:10:39.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: And
so again that fits

00:10:39.640 --> 00:10:41.975 align:middle line:90%
in with the Anunnaki legend.

00:10:41.975 --> 00:10:43.910 align:middle line:90%
But the thing to understand

00:10:43.910 --> 00:10:45.379 align:middle line:84%
about the Urantia
Book is it says

00:10:45.379 --> 00:10:48.615 align:middle line:84%
that the celestial
hierarchy of our planet

00:10:48.615 --> 00:10:52.986 align:middle line:84%
who sponsored these
interventions and incarnations,

00:10:52.986 --> 00:10:55.756 align:middle line:84%
they were unseen, they
actually went to the dark side

00:10:55.756 --> 00:10:58.058 align:middle line:84%
which is a very, very
rare event on a planet

00:10:58.058 --> 00:10:59.993 align:middle line:84%
when the angels go
to the dark side.

00:10:59.993 --> 00:11:01.395 align:middle line:90%
But this is sort of overseen

00:11:01.395 --> 00:11:04.097 align:middle line:84%
by angelic beings
that are a hierarchy.

00:11:04.097 --> 00:11:08.235 align:middle line:84%
And fairly up in the
hierarchy someone named Lucifer

00:11:08.235 --> 00:11:10.370 align:middle line:90%
went astray.

00:11:10.370 --> 00:11:14.207 align:middle line:84%
And his lieutenant Satan, a
real person, with him went

00:11:14.207 --> 00:11:17.778 align:middle line:84%
around to various planets
to try to corrupt them.

00:11:17.778 --> 00:11:21.381 align:middle line:84%
Actually their gospel was
God doesn't really exist.

00:11:21.381 --> 00:11:23.016 align:middle line:90%
That was at the core of this.

00:11:23.016 --> 00:11:25.452 align:middle line:84%
And we're free to
do what we want.

00:11:25.452 --> 00:11:29.222 align:middle line:84%
And so down from that
teaching comes the sort

00:11:29.222 --> 00:11:33.260 align:middle line:84%
of satanic tradition, the dark
traditions of this planet.

00:11:33.260 --> 00:11:37.230 align:middle line:84%
And that was then taught by
these groups on the ground

00:11:37.230 --> 00:11:41.033 align:middle line:84%
who were interbreeding who were
supervised by these dark beings.

00:11:41.033 --> 00:11:44.938 align:middle line:84%
So that's where we get
the Illuminati bloodlines.

00:11:44.938 --> 00:11:46.139 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: What's interesting

00:11:46.139 --> 00:11:49.509 align:middle line:84%
about that is even though
this was all an aspect

00:11:49.509 --> 00:11:52.079 align:middle line:84%
of an angelic realm
as you're saying,

00:11:52.079 --> 00:11:56.383 align:middle line:84%
the freedom of choice
exists all through.

00:11:56.383 --> 00:11:59.719 align:middle line:84%
It's not as though their
efforts were thwarted.

00:11:59.719 --> 00:12:02.122 align:middle line:90%
There was no intervention.

00:12:02.122 --> 00:12:04.224 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Regina,
I'm so glad you brought

00:12:04.224 --> 00:12:06.293 align:middle line:90%
up that issue of free will.

00:12:06.293 --> 00:12:08.995 align:middle line:84%
Angels have free will,
humans have free will.

00:12:08.995 --> 00:12:12.499 align:middle line:84%
That's the core of the
theology of the Urantia Book.

00:12:12.499 --> 00:12:15.302 align:middle line:84%
It also is Christian
theology and other theologies.

00:12:15.302 --> 00:12:20.974 align:middle line:84%
We are valued so much by the
divine that we're given freedom.

00:12:20.974 --> 00:12:23.877 align:middle line:84%
But there's always correcting
influences coming in.

00:12:23.877 --> 00:12:25.178 align:middle line:90%
So the Urantia Book states

00:12:25.178 --> 00:12:29.116 align:middle line:84%
that after the first
two major interventions

00:12:29.116 --> 00:12:33.753 align:middle line:84%
on the planet went astray, they
sent one after another prophet,

00:12:33.753 --> 00:12:36.723 align:middle line:84%
teacher and mission
to correct us.

00:12:36.723 --> 00:12:39.392 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Do they give similar
names that we would be familiar

00:12:39.392 --> 00:12:41.128 align:middle line:84%
with or entities
we'd be familiar

00:12:41.128 --> 00:12:43.330 align:middle line:90%
with as those who were sent?

00:12:43.330 --> 00:12:44.664 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: Yeah, certain ones.

00:12:44.664 --> 00:12:47.801 align:middle line:84%
Certainly the Hebrew prophets
were part of this program.

00:12:47.801 --> 00:12:50.003 align:middle line:90%
And in particular Melchizedek.

00:12:50.003 --> 00:12:53.140 align:middle line:84%
Melchizedek is a name you hear
in the new age all the time.

00:12:53.140 --> 00:12:55.842 align:middle line:84%
So if you are interested in
Melchizedek look at the chapters

00:12:55.842 --> 00:12:58.545 align:middle line:84%
about Makavec [phonetic]
and Melchizedek is the name

00:12:58.545 --> 00:13:00.680 align:middle line:84%
of this person who
actually incarnated

00:13:00.680 --> 00:13:04.784 align:middle line:84%
on an emergency mission to
correct all these problems.

00:13:04.784 --> 00:13:09.122 align:middle line:84%
And he had a big problem because
when he incarnated there was

00:13:09.122 --> 00:13:12.192 align:middle line:90%
pandemonium on the planet.

00:13:12.192 --> 00:13:15.829 align:middle line:84%
This was the time of the rise
of the Egyptian priesthood

00:13:15.829 --> 00:13:19.166 align:middle line:84%
which was oppressive,
of the Brahman caste

00:13:19.166 --> 00:13:21.234 align:middle line:90%
in India which was oppressive.

00:13:21.234 --> 00:13:25.172 align:middle line:84%
And all around the planet there
were these oppressive religions.

00:13:25.172 --> 00:13:29.576 align:middle line:84%
And his mission was to teach
a liberating religion actually

00:13:29.576 --> 00:13:30.810 align:middle line:90%
to the world.

00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:33.346 align:middle line:84%
And so the Melchizedek
teachings which are unknown

00:13:33.346 --> 00:13:36.416 align:middle line:84%
to the world other than the
fact that Melchizedek appeared

00:13:36.416 --> 00:13:38.518 align:middle line:90%
to Abraham in Genesis.

00:13:38.518 --> 00:13:40.253 align:middle line:84%
It says this guy just
walks into his tent

00:13:40.253 --> 00:13:43.190 align:middle line:84%
and his name is Melchizedek,
and he's a priest

00:13:43.190 --> 00:13:45.058 align:middle line:90%
after the order of Melchizedek.

00:13:45.058 --> 00:13:47.360 align:middle line:84%
So that's where this comes
from, it's a Hebrew term.

00:13:47.360 --> 00:13:51.198 align:middle line:84%
So historically in the Bible it
refers to this mysterious guy

00:13:51.198 --> 00:13:54.234 align:middle line:84%
that shows up out of nowhere
and says to Abraham you're going

00:13:54.234 --> 00:13:58.838 align:middle line:84%
to start a new race that will
numbered as many as the stars.

00:13:58.838 --> 00:14:02.943 align:middle line:84%
So you can take that passage
and come to the Urantia Book

00:14:02.943 --> 00:14:06.012 align:middle line:84%
and then get a complete
background on who this guy was.

00:14:06.012 --> 00:14:07.847 align:middle line:90%
So this is around 2000 B.C.

00:14:07.847 --> 00:14:09.516 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: What about
prior to that?

00:14:09.516 --> 00:14:11.718 align:middle line:84%
Were interventions
sent prior to that,

00:14:11.718 --> 00:14:15.288 align:middle line:84%
some of the more ancient
historical figures even?

00:14:15.288 --> 00:14:18.625 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: There was
always the good angels.

00:14:18.625 --> 00:14:22.796 align:middle line:84%
So most of the Angelicos
went dark.

00:14:22.796 --> 00:14:24.698 align:middle line:90%
The other part was still active.

00:14:24.698 --> 00:14:25.532 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: I see.

00:14:25.532 --> 00:14:26.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: They were split.

00:14:26.600 --> 00:14:28.301 align:middle line:84%
And so the good angels
were always trying

00:14:28.301 --> 00:14:29.903 align:middle line:90%
to stop what was happening.

00:14:29.903 --> 00:14:31.905 align:middle line:84%
The other thing very important
is, it's a little complicated,

00:14:31.905 --> 00:14:36.176 align:middle line:84%
but within the original group
I mentioned 500,000 years ago

00:14:36.176 --> 00:14:37.577 align:middle line:90%
that split.

00:14:37.577 --> 00:14:39.913 align:middle line:84%
So one part of that went dark,
the other part did not go dark.

00:14:39.913 --> 00:14:43.283 align:middle line:84%
And that part continued
a tradition of the light.

00:14:43.283 --> 00:14:44.384 align:middle line:90%
They were like light workers.

00:14:44.384 --> 00:14:46.186 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So now was
that a similar split

00:14:46.186 --> 00:14:47.654 align:middle line:84%
to what Sitchin would
have written

00:14:47.654 --> 00:14:49.789 align:middle line:84%
about between Incan
[phonetic] and Leo?

00:14:49.789 --> 00:14:50.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: I think so.

00:14:50.790 --> 00:14:52.459 align:middle line:90%
The Sitchin, yeah --

00:14:52.459 --> 00:14:54.361 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: I know there
were misinterpretations.

00:14:54.361 --> 00:14:56.696 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people say the
work was highly flawed,

00:14:56.696 --> 00:14:58.632 align:middle line:84%
but there is also
some truth to it.

00:14:58.632 --> 00:15:01.468 align:middle line:84%
So I'm just saying in broad
strokes might it have been

00:15:01.468 --> 00:15:03.036 align:middle line:90%
that little [inaudible] split.

00:15:03.036 --> 00:15:04.504 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Yeah, I would
agree with that in a broad way.

00:15:04.504 --> 00:15:06.873 align:middle line:90%
Also amazingly the time line

00:15:06.873 --> 00:15:08.908 align:middle line:84%
that Sitchin gives
is almost identical

00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:10.143 align:middle line:90%
to the Urantia time line.

00:15:10.143 --> 00:15:11.344 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yes, it is.

00:15:11.344 --> 00:15:12.746 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Urantia time
is 500,000 years ago.

00:15:12.746 --> 00:15:17.550 align:middle line:84%
The rebellion is 200,000 years
ago with the Nibiru Anunnaki.

00:15:17.550 --> 00:15:19.686 align:middle line:84%
The Urantia Book says
the same time line

00:15:19.686 --> 00:15:21.254 align:middle line:90%
around 200,000 years ago.

00:15:21.254 --> 00:15:23.723 align:middle line:84%
So actually they have
300,000 good years.

00:15:23.723 --> 00:15:25.358 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And it's
interesting, too,

00:15:25.358 --> 00:15:27.327 align:middle line:84%
because Sitchin's work
didn't come out until

00:15:27.327 --> 00:15:29.496 align:middle line:90%
after all of this, right?

00:15:29.496 --> 00:15:31.431 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Right, and I
don't think he was aware of --

00:15:31.431 --> 00:15:32.198 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And he
wasn't aware of it.

00:15:32.198 --> 00:15:32.966 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: -- this.

00:15:32.966 --> 00:15:34.033 align:middle line:90%
And I've tried to find --

00:15:34.033 --> 00:15:35.368 align:middle line:84%
people can write a
bridge between the two

00:15:35.368 --> 00:15:37.671 align:middle line:84%
which nobody is doing it
yet, maybe I'll do it,

00:15:37.671 --> 00:15:39.439 align:middle line:90%
but there definitely is.

00:15:39.439 --> 00:15:42.908 align:middle line:84%
Except he says that the
Anunnaki are from planet X

00:15:42.908 --> 00:15:44.244 align:middle line:90%
and that's hard to prove.

00:15:44.244 --> 00:15:47.647 align:middle line:84%
And the Urantia says something
more interesting I think,

00:15:47.647 --> 00:15:48.982 align:middle line:90%
more explanatory.

00:15:48.982 --> 00:15:51.384 align:middle line:84%
But it's kind of the same
morphology so to speak.

00:15:51.384 --> 00:15:53.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Okay, so here we are
the second split you say is a

00:15:53.920 --> 00:15:55.188 align:middle line:84%
couple hundred thousand
years ago.

00:15:55.188 --> 00:15:57.023 align:middle line:90%
What happened then?

00:15:57.023 --> 00:15:58.491 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: After
the rebellion --

00:15:58.491 --> 00:15:59.526 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Yeah,
after the rebellion --

00:15:59.526 --> 00:16:00.794 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: [Inaudible]
rebellion,

00:16:00.794 --> 00:16:04.731 align:middle line:84%
so as I said the first
avatar group, I call it that,

00:16:04.731 --> 00:16:07.033 align:middle line:84%
the Urantia Book doesn't,
that first group split;

00:16:07.033 --> 00:16:12.005 align:middle line:84%
60 out of the 100 went to
the dark side procedure

00:16:12.005 --> 00:16:14.641 align:middle line:84%
which was do whatever
you want to do.

00:16:14.641 --> 00:16:20.313 align:middle line:84%
And 40 of them remained
loyal to the divine plan.

00:16:20.313 --> 00:16:24.084 align:middle line:84%
They set up a settlement
actually in an area north

00:16:24.084 --> 00:16:27.287 align:middle line:84%
of the Mesopotamia which is
where all this was happening.

00:16:27.287 --> 00:16:30.523 align:middle line:84%
And their leader was someone
named Van [assumed spelling].

00:16:30.523 --> 00:16:32.726 align:middle line:84%
And Van continues --
these were immortals.

00:16:32.726 --> 00:16:37.964 align:middle line:84%
So he continued all the way
down upholding these traditions

00:16:37.964 --> 00:16:39.332 align:middle line:90%
and sending out emissaries

00:16:39.332 --> 00:16:43.937 align:middle line:84%
for all those year while the
dark group was fighting them,

00:16:43.937 --> 00:16:44.971 align:middle line:90%
literally fighting them.

00:16:44.971 --> 00:16:47.340 align:middle line:84%
And there's now new
channeled material

00:16:47.340 --> 00:16:50.777 align:middle line:84%
from Timothy Widley [phonetic]
a very important author

00:16:50.777 --> 00:16:54.814 align:middle line:84%
who is brought through eight
volume history of what happened

00:16:54.814 --> 00:16:57.516 align:middle line:84%
in this period that is
not in the Urantia Book.

00:16:57.516 --> 00:17:00.120 align:middle line:84%
It's controversial, but it's
very good and very coherent.

00:17:00.120 --> 00:17:02.956 align:middle line:84%
And this tells the
story of the battle

00:17:02.956 --> 00:17:06.158 align:middle line:84%
between these two groups
that was planet wide.

00:17:06.158 --> 00:17:09.995 align:middle line:84%
And does uphold this theory
you hear in other places

00:17:09.995 --> 00:17:12.966 align:middle line:84%
that the developed
technology, advanced technology

00:17:12.966 --> 00:17:14.701 align:middle line:90%
and a weaponized technology,

00:17:14.701 --> 00:17:18.638 align:middle line:84%
they had to because the dark
side beings were weaponizing.

00:17:18.638 --> 00:17:21.207 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So would this be
reflecting then the period

00:17:21.207 --> 00:17:23.510 align:middle line:84%
of history we would know
as the Atlantean period?

00:17:23.510 --> 00:17:25.745 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: The Atlantean
period and even previous

00:17:25.745 --> 00:17:27.947 align:middle line:90%
to the Atlantean period.

00:17:27.947 --> 00:17:29.482 align:middle line:90%
And these cultures spread out.

00:17:29.482 --> 00:17:34.020 align:middle line:84%
And the Van's culture, the
light worker culture, went east,

00:17:34.020 --> 00:17:38.358 align:middle line:84%
went to India, China and
then set up the Lemuria

00:17:38.358 --> 00:17:40.460 align:middle line:84%
in the Pacific, and that's
not in the Urantia Book.

00:17:40.460 --> 00:17:42.796 align:middle line:84%
So this is a new
revelation, it's not proved.

00:17:42.796 --> 00:17:46.232 align:middle line:84%
And then the Caligastia group,
it's known as Caligastia,

00:17:46.232 --> 00:17:47.367 align:middle line:90%
Caligastia was the head

00:17:47.367 --> 00:17:51.604 align:middle line:84%
of the planetary angels
who really went dark.

00:17:51.604 --> 00:17:54.841 align:middle line:84%
This group was more
around the Mediterranean.

00:17:54.841 --> 00:17:58.611 align:middle line:84%
And so these were warring
parties for thousands of years

00:17:58.611 --> 00:18:01.481 align:middle line:84%
until they had an
atomic war according

00:18:01.481 --> 00:18:04.117 align:middle line:84%
to Widley not according to
the Urantia Book, unproven.

00:18:04.117 --> 00:18:06.052 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: But in some other
texts they also speak of this.

00:18:06.052 --> 00:18:07.253 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Other texts
speak of this, too.

00:18:07.253 --> 00:18:11.257 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Even in the
Puranas I believe there is

00:18:11.257 --> 00:18:12.358 align:middle line:90%
atomic activity.

00:18:12.358 --> 00:18:13.593 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: Absolutely is.

00:18:13.593 --> 00:18:16.096 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So I have a
question here at this point.

00:18:16.096 --> 00:18:19.966 align:middle line:84%
What was it about -- was planet
Earth unique in some way?

00:18:19.966 --> 00:18:22.802 align:middle line:84%
What was it that
drove this huge split?

00:18:22.802 --> 00:18:25.839 align:middle line:84%
There had to be a
temptation of some kind.

00:18:25.839 --> 00:18:29.476 align:middle line:84%
What would have driven
these otherwise good natured

00:18:29.476 --> 00:18:34.347 align:middle line:84%
and intentioned beings into
this dark exploitive mode?

00:18:34.347 --> 00:18:35.782 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: That's
why we need to stick

00:18:35.782 --> 00:18:38.218 align:middle line:84%
that in the Urantia Book
to explain the background

00:18:38.218 --> 00:18:41.154 align:middle line:84%
and orientation because it talks
about life on other planets

