>> Regina: Exactly.

00:28:04.417 --> 00:28:05.051 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: I mean
it's kind of obvious.

00:28:05.051 --> 00:28:06.118 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Right.

00:28:06.118 --> 00:28:08.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: But this
is fairly radical

00:28:08.320 --> 00:28:11.390 align:middle line:84%
in that it says you might
as well not think too much

00:28:11.390 --> 00:28:13.225 align:middle line:84%
about environmental
sustainability unless you have

00:28:13.225 --> 00:28:19.165 align:middle line:84%
institutions that can implement
environmental regulation,

00:28:19.165 --> 00:28:20.433 align:middle line:90%
and you really don't.

00:28:20.433 --> 00:28:24.370 align:middle line:84%
I mean look at global warming,
look at climate change.

00:28:24.370 --> 00:28:26.305 align:middle line:84%
You really don't have the
ability to regulate it

00:28:26.305 --> 00:28:28.941 align:middle line:84%
because you don't have
sustainable institutions

00:28:28.941 --> 00:28:31.777 align:middle line:84%
that can make decisions,
