We've seen pretty close to that.

00:29:58.264 --> 00:29:59.732 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: We're seeing it, yes.

00:29:59.732 --> 00:30:01.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: So it's not
hard to believe that.

00:30:01.600 --> 00:30:04.470 align:middle line:84%
And they started saying that
before the collapse in 2008.

00:30:04.470 --> 00:30:06.305 align:middle line:90%
They were saying it in 2006.

00:30:06.305 --> 00:30:08.073 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, God, this
is it, it's happening,

00:30:08.073 --> 00:30:11.210 align:middle line:84%
2008 is what they're
saying, it's so soon.

00:30:11.210 --> 00:30:14.380 align:middle line:84%
But the system can
self-heal somewhat,

00:30:14.380 --> 00:30:18.150 align:middle line:84%
but really bailing themselves
out isn't going to work forever.

00:30:18.150 --> 00:30:20.019 align:middle line:84%
So they said, well, just
look at the evidence.

00:30:20.019 --> 00:30:22.121 align:middle line:84%
Or look at other civilizations
that have collapsed

00:30:22.121 --> 00:30:23.489 align:middle line:90%
and almost every single one.

00:30:23.489 --> 00:30:24.857 align:middle line:90%
I mean name one that didn't.

00:30:24.857 --> 00:30:29.061 align:middle line:84%
Every single one,
China or Roman Empire,

00:30:29.061 --> 00:30:32.131 align:middle line:84%
whatever it is these
empires have gone away.

00:30:32.131 --> 00:30:35.734 align:middle line:84%
So you, too, will go away but
this time on a planetary scale.

00:30:35.734 --> 00:30:38.571 align:middle line:84%
But I mean there will
be surviving structures

00:30:38.571 --> 00:30:41.473 align:middle line:84%
and libraries and things
will still survive.

00:30:41.473 --> 00:30:44.577 align:middle line:84%
But we're going to give you
something that's grass roots.

00:30:44.577 --> 00:30:47.012 align:middle line:84%
So their approach
is grass roots.

00:30:47.012 --> 00:30:49.014 align:middle line:90%
Which to me sounds pretty tough.

00:30:49.014 --> 00:30:50.516 align:middle line:90%
So citizens have to do it.

00:30:50.516 --> 00:30:53.085 align:middle line:84%
And then in these dialogues
and this is just one,

00:30:53.085 --> 00:30:55.688 align:middle line:84%
there's like 2,000 pages of
stuff, we got it down to 100.

00:30:55.688 --> 00:30:58.724 align:middle line:84%
We said how are we going to
get these people to do this?

00:30:58.724 --> 00:31:03.195 align:middle line:84%
They said people will run to
do this at a certain point

00:31:03.195 --> 00:31:04.463 align:middle line:90%
because they will want --

00:31:04.463 --> 00:31:05.631 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: I would agree.

00:31:05.631 --> 00:31:06.699 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: -- to
rebuild their institutions.

00:31:06.699 --> 00:31:08.801 align:middle line:84%
And they'll need a
methodology to do this,

00:31:08.801 --> 00:31:10.002 align:middle line:84%
and they'll need
something simple.

00:31:10.002 --> 00:31:11.971 align:middle line:84%
And there's plenty of
great stuff out there.

00:31:11.971 --> 00:31:15.341 align:middle line:84%
But we simplify it down
to three basic things.

00:31:15.341 --> 00:31:17.543 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Yes, and
then how to utilize that

00:31:17.543 --> 00:31:20.379 align:middle line:84%
and the participants and
the nature of their roles.

00:31:20.379 --> 00:31:23.682 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of this when you're
reading the book you have the

00:31:23.682 --> 00:31:26.852 align:middle line:84%
comments from the
entity that is involved,

00:31:26.852 --> 00:31:30.589 align:middle line:84%
the celestial being
named Monjoronson?

00:31:30.589 --> 00:31:33.025 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Monjoronson
or Monjoronson.

00:31:33.025 --> 00:31:35.894 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Okay, and so tell us
a little bit about this being.

00:31:35.894 --> 00:31:40.099 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Monjoronson is
a very high celestial being.

