00:34:09.915 --> 00:34:11.016 align:middle line:90%
in a book and there it is.

00:34:11.016 --> 00:34:12.884 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Right, so
let's talk about that.

00:34:12.884 --> 00:34:15.654 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about the
three core values they say is

00:34:15.654 --> 00:34:19.857 align:middle line:84%
absolutely necessary no matter
where you are in the cosmos

00:34:19.857 --> 00:34:24.129 align:middle line:84%
to have societies that function
well, bring the most out

00:34:24.129 --> 00:34:26.532 align:middle line:90%
and sustain themselves.

00:34:26.532 --> 00:34:29.735 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: So throughout
the cosmos there are billions

00:34:29.735 --> 00:34:32.504 align:middle line:84%
of inhabited planets
according the Urantia Book

00:34:32.504 --> 00:34:34.273 align:middle line:90%
and according to many others.

00:34:34.273 --> 00:34:38.310 align:middle line:84%
If you observe how they become
sustainable there's a certain

00:34:38.310 --> 00:34:39.844 align:middle line:84%
set of principles
that are always there,

00:34:39.844 --> 00:34:42.181 align:middle line:90%
and they're really common sense.

00:34:42.181 --> 00:34:44.683 align:middle line:84%
Sustainability socially
means, number one,

00:34:44.683 --> 00:34:47.085 align:middle line:90%
you can't have inequality.

00:34:47.085 --> 00:34:49.421 align:middle line:84%
Because eventually you're going
to have a revolution of the poor

00:34:49.421 --> 00:34:52.858 align:middle line:84%
versus -- so that's
not sustainable.

00:34:52.858 --> 00:34:56.829 align:middle line:84%
So you say, well, okay
now we have equality

00:34:56.829 --> 00:34:58.897 align:middle line:84%
but that's not going
to be sustainable

00:34:58.897 --> 00:35:00.599 align:middle line:90%
because pretty soon you're going

00:35:00.599 --> 00:35:02.634 align:middle line:84%
to realize we don't have
a quality of life here.

00:35:02.634 --> 00:35:03.902 align:middle line:90%
We're like in prison here.

00:35:03.902 --> 00:35:06.371 align:middle line:84%
Everybody is equal, and
that's what communism is like.

00:35:06.371 --> 00:35:08.540 align:middle line:84%
So we need to add
quality of life.

00:35:08.540 --> 00:35:10.542 align:middle line:84%
I mean everybody is
surviving and not starving,

00:35:10.542 --> 00:35:12.711 align:middle line:90%
so let's add quality of life.

00:35:12.711 --> 00:35:14.847 align:middle line:90%
That's the second value.

00:35:14.847 --> 00:35:18.217 align:middle line:90%
The third value is growth.

00:35:18.217 --> 00:35:22.488 align:middle line:84%
So imagine a situation where
everyone in this situation,

00:35:22.488 --> 00:35:25.457 align:middle line:84%
let's say a country,
everybody is equal,

00:35:25.457 --> 00:35:28.694 align:middle line:84%
everybody has got quality of
life and everybody is growing,

00:35:28.694 --> 00:35:32.631 align:middle line:84%
personal growth, spiritually
growing, self-realization.

00:35:32.631 --> 00:35:34.399 align:middle line:84%
Where do you find
that happening?

00:35:34.399 --> 00:35:38.637 align:middle line:84%
Well, maybe Shangri-La or
something but it's utopia.

00:35:38.637 --> 00:35:41.373 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Maybe kind of in a
few intentional communities,

00:35:41.373 --> 00:35:43.909 align:middle line:84%
but they're having issues
of their own as well, yeah.

00:35:43.909 --> 00:35:45.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: That's
really the idea

00:35:45.110 --> 00:35:46.678 align:middle line:84%
of an intentional
community, isn't it,

00:35:46.678 --> 00:35:48.580 align:middle line:90%
it's equal and they're growing.

00:35:48.580 --> 00:35:54.887 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so it's like a utopian
vision, but they use logic.

00:35:54.887 --> 00:35:57.523 align:middle line:84%
And they say, look, I
mean think about it,

00:35:57.523 --> 00:36:00.559 align:middle line:84%
where do you find
something stable

00:36:00.559 --> 00:36:01.994 align:middle line:90%
that doesn't have these three?

00:36:01.994 --> 00:36:03.829 align:middle line:90%
Like a family for example.

00:36:03.829 --> 00:36:07.065 align:middle line:84%
I mean the children ought
to have certain rights.

00:36:07.065 --> 00:36:10.903 align:middle line:84%
And it's not that the parents
are dictating to the children.

00:36:10.903 --> 00:36:12.738 align:middle line:84%
So you need some
kind of equality

00:36:12.738 --> 00:36:14.506 align:middle line:90%
of rights, equal rights.

00:36:14.506 --> 00:36:15.507 align:middle line:90%
A quality of life.

00:36:15.507 --> 00:36:16.775 align:middle line:84%
If the family doesn't
have quality

00:36:16.775 --> 00:36:19.545 align:middle line:84%
of life the kids act out,
they start getting crazy.

00:36:19.545 --> 00:36:25.284 align:middle line:84%
And if people aren't growing
then they aren't growing up.

00:36:25.284 --> 00:36:26.685 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Right.

00:36:26.685 --> 00:36:30.088 align:middle line:84%
And it's interesting because in
our cultures now growth always

00:36:30.088 --> 00:36:35.627 align:middle line:84%
seems to come at the expense
of the inequality issue.

00:36:35.627 --> 00:36:37.129 align:middle line:90%
Someone wins, someone loses,

00:36:37.129 --> 00:36:39.598 align:middle line:84%
someone exploits,
someone provides.

00:36:39.598 --> 00:36:44.436 align:middle line:84%
And when you look at just
our human personalities

00:36:44.436 --> 00:36:47.472 align:middle line:84%
and behavior you have
your A type personalities,

00:36:47.472 --> 00:36:49.441 align:middle line:84%
B type personalities
and so forth.

00:36:49.441 --> 00:36:53.412 align:middle line:84%
This is not eradicating
our native nature.

00:36:53.412 --> 00:36:57.015 align:middle line:84%
We can live within nature it
sounds like without having

00:36:57.015 --> 00:37:01.253 align:middle line:84%
to violate that inequality
issue for growth.

