00:37:15.334 --> 00:37:18.570 align:middle line:84%
And later when I was doing
this work I realized, oh,

00:37:18.570 --> 00:37:22.975 align:middle line:84%
this is the case of
the quality of life.

00:37:22.975 --> 00:37:25.243 align:middle line:84%
They have high quality
of life in aristocracies.

00:37:25.243 --> 00:37:27.279 align:middle line:90%
No wonder I like it.

00:37:27.279 --> 00:37:30.382 align:middle line:84%
Great music, great art, great
writing, poetry, all this stuff.

00:37:30.382 --> 00:37:31.783 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Food,
clothes, it's all there.

00:37:31.783 --> 00:37:33.652 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: All of it, and
they're growing as people.

00:37:33.652 --> 00:37:38.590 align:middle line:84%
But it's totally corrupt because
the peasants are repressed.

00:37:38.590 --> 00:37:42.060 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know if that exactly
responds to what you said.

00:37:42.060 --> 00:37:43.395 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yes.

00:37:43.395 --> 00:37:44.796 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: But it's just
the experience of this in once

00:37:44.796 --> 00:37:48.433 align:middle line:84%
in a life where you recognize
here I am living in the suburbs

00:37:48.433 --> 00:37:51.470 align:middle line:84%
of San Francisco where
I live in Marin County

00:37:51.470 --> 00:37:53.605 align:middle line:84%
where it's a great quality of
life, and I go over the bridge

00:37:53.605 --> 00:37:57.175 align:middle line:84%
to Oakland and it's really
sometimes quite a mess.

00:37:57.175 --> 00:37:58.377 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of
crime over there,

00:37:58.377 --> 00:38:00.545 align:middle line:84%
and that's just a
few miles away.

00:38:00.545 --> 00:38:03.148 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: I mean the
difference between Marin County

00:38:03.148 --> 00:38:05.851 align:middle line:84%
and certain areas of Oakland,
I've spent a lot of time in each

00:38:05.851 --> 00:38:08.453 align:middle line:84%
and was raised partially
in Marin County,

00:38:08.453 --> 00:38:09.955 align:middle line:84%
I mean here you're
looking at sort

00:38:09.955 --> 00:38:11.957 align:middle line:90%
of the best of the best in life.

00:38:11.957 --> 00:38:15.427 align:middle line:84%
Even the weather is
pretty much perfect.

00:38:15.427 --> 00:38:20.966 align:middle line:84%
Camelot. And then you go over
into Oakland into certain areas

00:38:20.966 --> 00:38:24.936 align:middle line:90%
of Oakland and it's so desolate.

00:38:24.936 --> 00:38:28.707 align:middle line:84%
Not only are there
not jasmine and roses

00:38:28.707 --> 00:38:32.244 align:middle line:84%
and beautiful things growing,
you're talking about dirt,

00:38:32.244 --> 00:38:36.415 align:middle line:84%
not even grass growing and
dogs and chain link fences,

00:38:36.415 --> 00:38:41.053 align:middle line:84%
and people whose eyes
are so sad, so empty,

00:38:41.053 --> 00:38:43.155 align:middle line:90%
so angry and desperate.

00:38:43.155 --> 00:38:46.391 align:middle line:84%
So close together these two
realities including the Oakland

00:38:46.391 --> 00:38:47.859 align:middle line:90%
Hills, from the Oakland Hills.

00:38:47.859 --> 00:38:49.528 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Yeah, just
come down the hill.

00:38:49.528 --> 00:38:51.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So that
isn't working.

00:38:51.530 --> 00:38:52.864 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Yeah,
that's not working.

00:38:52.864 --> 00:38:57.269 align:middle line:84%
So think of social
sustainability as a culture

00:38:57.269 --> 00:39:00.238 align:middle line:84%
where it's like a stool
where there's three legs.

00:39:00.238 --> 00:39:02.774 align:middle line:84%
Equality has to be
there, that's one leg.

00:39:02.774 --> 00:39:05.677 align:middle line:84%
The other leg is
quality of life.

00:39:05.677 --> 00:39:08.880 align:middle line:90%
And the third leg is growth.

00:39:08.880 --> 00:39:11.616 align:middle line:90%
The stool can be stable.

00:39:11.616 --> 00:39:15.253 align:middle line:84%
Oakland could be a stable place
and not have all this crime,

00:39:15.253 --> 00:39:18.256 align:middle line:84%
not have uprisings
like the occupation.

00:39:18.256 --> 00:39:21.259 align:middle line:84%
The occupied movement was an
uprise, it was a good uprising,

00:39:21.259 --> 00:39:25.330 align:middle line:84%
but it disrupts life to have
uprisings to try to fix things.

00:39:25.330 --> 00:39:27.699 align:middle line:84%
So you have to have that
stool that's stable.

00:39:27.699 --> 00:39:31.636 align:middle line:84%
And how you get that into these
institutions of government,

00:39:31.636 --> 00:39:34.973 align:middle line:84%
of business, industry
that's a big job.

00:39:34.973 --> 00:39:37.743 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: So it sounds
like the beings involved

00:39:37.743 --> 00:39:40.479 align:middle line:84%
with this were very
intentional, as you say,

00:39:40.479 --> 00:39:42.314 align:middle line:84%
in starting on a
grass roots level.

00:39:42.314 --> 00:39:45.350 align:middle line:84%
You can take a PTA
group or whatever

00:39:45.350 --> 00:39:47.686 align:middle line:84%
and really apply these
principles for something

00:39:47.686 --> 00:39:50.589 align:middle line:84%
of high function, and that's
not to make light of the PTA.

00:39:50.589 --> 00:39:53.458 align:middle line:84%
A lot of things happen in
the schools or not happening

00:39:53.458 --> 00:39:54.659 align:middle line:90%
in the school actually,

00:39:54.659 --> 00:39:57.395 align:middle line:84%
they can't get things done
there anymore starting

00:39:57.395 --> 00:39:59.231 align:middle line:84%
with raising the children
in the way they need

00:39:59.231 --> 00:40:02.234 align:middle line:84%
to define their own talents,
their own desires and so forth.

00:40:02.234 --> 00:40:04.169 align:middle line:84%
So let's talk about
where it begins.

00:40:04.169 --> 00:40:05.403 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Just
look at schools.

00:40:05.403 --> 00:40:08.073 align:middle line:84%
I mean schools there's
the sense of equality.

00:40:08.073 --> 00:40:11.910 align:middle line:84%
Everybody goes to school, either
public school or some kind

00:40:11.910 --> 00:40:15.147 align:middle line:84%
of education is required
as it should be.

00:40:15.147 --> 00:40:16.748 align:middle line:90%
So we're all equal.

00:40:16.748 --> 00:40:20.285 align:middle line:84%
We all go to junior,
elementary and high school.

00:40:20.285 --> 00:40:23.321 align:middle line:84%
But beyond that there's really
not much quality there unless

00:40:23.321 --> 00:40:27.459 align:middle line:84%
you go to a private school and
you get some quality there.

00:40:27.459 --> 00:40:29.494 align:middle line:90%
But are people really growing?

00:40:29.494 --> 00:40:32.164 align:middle line:84%
Well, we find a lot of
them are dropping out.

00:40:32.164 --> 00:40:35.233 align:middle line:84%
And so schools are
not sustainable.

00:40:35.233 --> 00:40:37.002 align:middle line:84%
I think that's obvious
to all of us.

00:40:37.002 --> 00:40:38.603 align:middle line:84%
So how would you get
that to be the case?

00:40:38.603 --> 00:40:40.906 align:middle line:84%
Well, we're going
to have a tax base

00:40:40.906 --> 00:40:44.276 align:middle line:84%
to fund high quality
education across the board.

00:40:44.276 --> 00:40:48.280 align:middle line:84%
No discrepancies by
race or class or region.

00:40:48.280 --> 00:40:51.116 align:middle line:84%
And so I think it's
straightforward.

00:40:51.116 --> 00:40:52.684 align:middle line:90%
You've got to have music.

00:40:52.684 --> 00:40:53.819 align:middle line:90%
You've got to have art.

00:40:53.819 --> 00:40:56.721 align:middle line:84%
You've got to have kids
learning about civics.

00:40:56.721 --> 00:41:00.358 align:middle line:90%
You've got math and science.

00:41:00.358 --> 00:41:02.561 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: And use their bodies.

00:41:02.561 --> 00:41:03.395 align:middle line:90%
>> Belitsos: What's that?

00:41:03.395 --> 00:41:04.362 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Physical education.

00:41:04.362 --> 00:41:05.664 align:middle line:84%
Let people use their
bodies again.

00:41:05.664 --> 00:41:08.033 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: That's it so
they can grow and be strong

00:41:08.033 --> 00:41:09.301 align:middle line:90%
and so all these things.

00:41:09.301 --> 00:41:11.203 align:middle line:84%
And also fostering
personal growth

00:41:11.203 --> 00:41:14.339 align:middle line:90%
in classes on personal growth.

00:41:14.339 --> 00:41:16.441 align:middle line:90%
Sex education is important, too.

00:41:16.441 --> 00:41:19.911 align:middle line:84%
And all that gives you a
socially sustainable tool.

00:41:19.911 --> 00:41:22.881 align:middle line:84%
So if you wanted to do
a design you would start

00:41:22.881 --> 00:41:25.617 align:middle line:84%
as a social sustainability
design team.

00:41:25.617 --> 00:41:27.219 align:middle line:90%
You would instigate a team.

00:41:27.219 --> 00:41:30.455 align:middle line:84%
And you would invite people
who are interested in education

00:41:30.455 --> 00:41:33.825 align:middle line:84%
or in education or teachers,
and you have a citizens' group

00:41:33.825 --> 00:41:35.827 align:middle line:90%
that would have, if I may,

00:41:35.827 --> 00:41:37.028 align:middle line:84%
talk about the structure
of the group.

00:41:37.028 --> 00:41:38.096 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: I would like to
talk about the structure

00:41:38.096 --> 00:41:40.665 align:middle line:84%
and the roles various
people play, yes.

00:41:40.665 --> 00:41:42.067 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: So you
have like the organizer.

00:41:42.067 --> 00:41:44.436 align:middle line:90%
The organizer has division.

00:41:44.436 --> 00:41:46.137 align:middle line:90%
We've got to fix schools.

00:41:46.137 --> 00:41:48.573 align:middle line:84%
So let's try to do
this in Oakland.

00:41:48.573 --> 00:41:51.743 align:middle line:84%
I will recruit some people, not
too many, six, seven, eight,

00:41:51.743 --> 00:41:56.515 align:middle line:84%
nine people to be in this
committee really, it's SSDT,

00:41:56.515 --> 00:41:58.617 align:middle line:84%
social sustainability
design team

00:41:58.617 --> 00:42:00.252 align:middle line:90%
or just team or design team.

00:42:00.252 --> 00:42:03.388 align:middle line:84%
And you follow the procedure
in the procedure in the book

00:42:03.388 --> 00:42:07.325 align:middle line:84%
which is you get a facilitator,
not necessarily the organizer,

00:42:07.325 --> 00:42:09.127 align:middle line:84%
someone who is good
at facilitation.

00:42:09.127 --> 00:42:11.897 align:middle line:84%
That person is going
to set up a procedure

00:42:11.897 --> 00:42:14.132 align:middle line:84%
so that the others
can do their job.

00:42:14.132 --> 00:42:18.703 align:middle line:84%
And the other jobs are
inquiring, questioning.

00:42:18.703 --> 00:42:21.072 align:middle line:84%
So you have several members
who are good at that,

00:42:21.072 --> 00:42:23.775 align:middle line:84%
good at questioning,
good at researching.

00:42:23.775 --> 00:42:27.979 align:middle line:84%
And you actually have meetings
where they're asking questions

00:42:27.979 --> 00:42:29.848 align:middle line:90%
and having deliberations.

00:42:29.848 --> 00:42:32.250 align:middle line:84%
And there's another role
called the recorder,

00:42:32.250 --> 00:42:36.388 align:middle line:84%
and the recorder is taking
it all down and providing --

00:42:36.388 --> 00:42:38.323 align:middle line:84%
it's more than just
being a secretary.

00:42:38.323 --> 00:42:39.991 align:middle line:90%
They're providing good summaries

00:42:39.991 --> 00:42:41.393 align:middle line:84%
for the next meeting,
for example.

00:42:41.393 --> 00:42:44.829 align:middle line:84%
And they're reading back, this
is what we're now talking about.

00:42:44.829 --> 00:42:48.900 align:middle line:84%
So you get into a process
for weeks or months even

00:42:48.900 --> 00:42:52.504 align:middle line:84%
until everybody agrees that
we've hit the bottom of this.

00:42:52.504 --> 00:42:55.373 align:middle line:84%
We've got to the
core assumptions.

00:42:55.373 --> 00:42:57.509 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And that's
a big thing.

00:42:57.509 --> 00:43:00.178 align:middle line:84%
Assumptions, every
assumption has to be evaluated,

00:43:00.178 --> 00:43:03.248 align:middle line:84%
but not only that and torn
apart and restructured

00:43:03.248 --> 00:43:06.017 align:middle line:84%
because assumptions are at
the base of all dysfunction.

00:43:06.017 --> 00:43:08.219 align:middle line:90%
You have incorrect assumptions.

00:43:08.219 --> 00:43:10.355 align:middle line:84%
And in addition to that
you have people coming

00:43:10.355 --> 00:43:13.491 align:middle line:84%
and maybe running their
own agenda for maybe sort

00:43:13.491 --> 00:43:15.327 align:middle line:90%
of egoic or personal gain.

00:43:15.327 --> 00:43:17.629 align:middle line:90%
That's not going to work there.

00:43:17.629 --> 00:43:22.133 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: If you get the
group aligned spiritually

00:43:22.133 --> 00:43:25.337 align:middle line:84%
with one another, and
there needs to be exercises

00:43:25.337 --> 00:43:29.074 align:middle line:84%
and we have them in the
book of prayer together,

00:43:29.074 --> 00:43:33.178 align:middle line:84%
of energetic alignment so that
you don't have people acting

00:43:33.178 --> 00:43:35.480 align:middle line:90%
out egoically more or less.

00:43:35.480 --> 00:43:37.916 align:middle line:84%
But if somebody does
you call them on it.

00:43:37.916 --> 00:43:39.985 align:middle line:84%
So there are methods
for sort of --

00:43:39.985 --> 00:43:46.958 align:middle line:84%
facilitation methods of
collaborative deliberation

00:43:46.958 --> 00:43:50.996 align:middle line:84%
where you are honest with one
another because you've bonded

00:43:50.996 --> 00:43:52.964 align:middle line:90%
and so you can be honest.

00:43:52.964 --> 00:43:56.234 align:middle line:84%
So it should be a lot of fun
to meet with colleagues and get

00:43:56.234 --> 00:43:58.303 align:middle line:84%
to the bottom of what is
the issue with education.

00:43:58.303 --> 00:44:01.206 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: It's really
a pure kind of analysis.

00:44:01.206 --> 00:44:02.841 align:middle line:90%
It's not agenda driven other

00:44:02.841 --> 00:44:06.344 align:middle line:84%
than the agreed upon sole
agenda of the group, right?

00:44:06.344 --> 00:44:09.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: It's like everybody
becoming a Socratic philosopher

00:44:09.180 --> 00:44:09.881 align:middle line:90%
in a way.

00:44:09.881 --> 00:44:11.616 align:middle line:90%
It's pure in that sense.

00:44:11.616 --> 00:44:12.884 align:middle line:90%
We just have questions.

00:44:12.884 --> 00:44:14.185 align:middle line:90%
We don't have answer.

00:44:14.185 --> 00:44:15.553 align:middle line:90%
I may think I have answers.

00:44:15.553 --> 00:44:18.490 align:middle line:84%
I'll put them on the table, but
we're going to tear that up.

00:44:18.490 --> 00:44:21.026 align:middle line:90%
We're going to get below that,

00:44:21.026 --> 00:44:22.594 align:middle line:84%
and that's really
what philosophers do.

00:44:22.594 --> 00:44:25.563 align:middle line:84%
They get to the assumptions
underneath these conclusions.

00:44:25.563 --> 00:44:28.533 align:middle line:84%
And that's what a real
mature society does.

00:44:28.533 --> 00:44:30.135 align:middle line:84%
That's what Congress
should be doing.

00:44:30.135 --> 00:44:33.004 align:middle line:84%
Congress should be having
deliberative discussions

00:44:33.004 --> 00:44:36.508 align:middle line:84%
about the assumptions behind
all of these programs.

00:44:36.508 --> 00:44:38.777 align:middle line:84%
Instead it's at this
other level of just --

00:44:38.777 --> 00:44:40.812 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Oh, it's so broken
it's not even worth addressing.

00:44:40.812 --> 00:44:43.848 align:middle line:84%
It really does have to be
refashioned from the ground up.

00:44:43.848 --> 00:44:45.784 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: They don't
have true debates.

00:44:45.784 --> 00:44:47.185 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: No.

00:44:47.185 --> 00:44:48.753 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Those committees
are just dominated by parties.

00:44:48.753 --> 00:44:49.621 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Absolutely.

00:44:49.621 --> 00:44:50.855 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: You
abolish parties.

00:44:50.855 --> 00:44:54.692 align:middle line:84%
You would have each
individual in the light of God

00:44:54.692 --> 00:44:57.462 align:middle line:84%
and the truth is
getting to the --

00:44:57.462 --> 00:45:00.799 align:middle line:84%
really like Socrates
asking the hard questions.

00:45:00.799 --> 00:45:02.300 align:middle line:90%
So every citizen being

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:05.036 align:middle line:84%
like Socrates that's
an ideal society.

00:45:05.036 --> 00:45:06.705 align:middle line:90%
That's real civic participation.

00:45:06.705 --> 00:45:09.941 align:middle line:84%
And it's also fun to do
because I've done some of this.

00:45:09.941 --> 00:45:11.776 align:middle line:84%
And if it's something
you care about --

00:45:11.776 --> 00:45:12.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Regina: Yeah.

00:45:12.610 --> 00:45:13.678 align:middle line:90%
No, to me it sounds exciting.

00:45:13.678 --> 00:45:15.747 align:middle line:84%
The process itself
sounds exciting.

00:45:15.747 --> 00:45:19.517 align:middle line:84%
And so as you have people
that are participating

00:45:19.517 --> 00:45:22.954 align:middle line:84%
in these various roles, first
of all you just ask questions,

00:45:22.954 --> 00:45:27.058 align:middle line:84%
and you get down to stripping
bear some incorrect assumptions

00:45:27.058 --> 00:45:29.794 align:middle line:84%
that have been creating a
dysfunctional environment,

00:45:29.794 --> 00:45:30.829 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:45:30.829 --> 00:45:31.930 align:middle line:90%
Then what?

00:45:31.930 --> 00:45:33.731 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: Also you're
out doing research.

00:45:33.731 --> 00:45:35.033 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: And you're
out doing research.

00:45:35.033 --> 00:45:36.367 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: You're actually
reading the literature --

00:45:36.367 --> 00:45:37.669 align:middle line:84%
>> Regina: Your inquiring
minds are doing the research.

00:45:37.669 --> 00:45:40.305 align:middle line:84%
>> Belitsos: The inquiring
group is doing the research.

00:45:40.305 --> 00:45:42.207 align:middle line:84%
Anybody can do research,
bring it to the table

00:45:42.207 --> 00:45:43.508 align:middle line:90%
and say this is what we know.

00:45:43.508 --> 00:45:45.076 align:middle line:84%
This is the data we
have from the Department

00:45:45.076 --> 00:45:47.212 align:middle line:90%
of Education right now.

00:45:47.212 --> 00:45:49.514 align:middle line:84%
This is the data we have
from the Oakland Department

00:45:49.514 --> 00:45:51.883 align:middle line:84%
of Education and here's
what we're facing here.

00:45:51.883 --> 00:45:54.319 align:middle line:84%
So you'd have that
in, the data has to be

00:45:54.319 --> 00:45:55.620 align:middle line:90%
in front of you as well.

00:45:55.620 --> 00:45:59.124 align:middle line:84%
Here are some other designs
that we've heard about.

00:45:59.124 --> 00:46:02.594 align:middle line:90%
Let's look at their designs.

00:46:02.594 --> 00:46:05.196 align:middle line:84%
So whatever you could
bring into --

00:46:05.196 --> 00:46:06.731 align:middle line:84%
your own experience
as a teacher.

00:46:06.731 --> 00:46:09.067 align:middle line:84%
Here's what I found
out as a teacher.

00:46:09.067 --> 00:46:14.005 align:middle line:84%
My kids were a mess because
some of them came in hungry.

00:46:14.005 --> 00:46:15.240 align:middle line:90%
You've got to deal with that.

00:46:15.240 --> 00:46:18.309 align:middle line:84%
We've got to make sure
kids are getting breakfast.

00:46:18.309 --> 00:46:19.711 align:middle line:84%
Real basic things
are brought in.

00:46:19.711 --> 00:46:23.615 align:middle line:84%
You just write this stuff all
up and have a lot of notes

00:46:23.615 --> 00:46:26.951 align:middle line:84%
until you get to -- when you're
ready, you don't know quite

00:46:26.951 --> 00:46:29.954 align:middle line:84%
when you're ready until
you're ready, when you know

00:46:29.954 --> 00:46:35.226 align:middle line:84%
that we can give a summary that
includes all three core values

00:46:35.226 --> 00:46:38.096 align:middle line:90%
of social sustainability.

